# patchbay:research — fetch failures log
#
# Schema (one entry per failed fetch attempt):
#   - timestamp:    ISO 8601
#   - url:          The URL that failed
#   - tier_attempted: 1 (static) | 2 (browser) | 3 (visual)
#   - http_status:  HTTP status code (or null if non-HTTP error)
#   - reason:       Short machine-readable reason (cloudflare-block | bot-detected | js-required | rate-limited | paywall | 404 | timeout | other)
#   - reason_detail: Free-text human-readable explanation
#   - suggested_escalation: 2 | 3 | manual-paste | skip
#   - last_attempted: ISO 8601 of most recent retry
#   - retry_count: int
#
# Format: one JSON object per line (jsonl).
# Production behavior: append-only. User reviews this file and decides which
# entries to escalate (move to a separate "queue" file for tier-2/3 attempts).

